title: IMD forecasts heavy to very heavy rainfall across country - Newsonair
article_text: India Meteorological Department (IMD) has forecast heavy to very heavy rainfall over Arunachal Pradesh, Assam and Meghalaya, Bihar, Himachal Pradesh, Kerala and Mahe, West Bengal, Tamil Nadu, Uttar Pradesh and Uttarakhand today. IMD predicted heavy rainfall over Haryana, Chandigarh, Delhi, Jammu and Kashmir, Ladakh, Lakshadweep, Madhya Pradesh, Nagaland, Manipur, Mizoram and Tripura. According to IMD, Bihar, Coastal Andhra Pradesh, Gangetic West Bengal, Jammu and Kashmir, Ladakh, Jharkhand, Karnataka and West Madhya Pradesh can experience thunderstorm accompanied with lightning and gusty winds.

title: UP Weather Update: Heavy Rain, Lightning Alert In Kanpur, Lucknow, Ayodhya, 43 Other Districts Today, Check Forecast - The Daily Jagran
article_text: By Nidhi GiriMon, 04 Aug 2025 09:38 AM (IST)Source:JND Related Articles              UP Weather Update: The India Meteorological Department (IMD) has forecast heavy rain in 46 districts in the next 24 hours, Additionally, there is a possibility of thunderstorms and lightning in 64 districts. On Sunday, many districts of western and eastern Uttar Pradesh received rain throughout the day.          Heavy Rain Alert In THESE Districts     Senior Meteorologist Dr Atul Kumar Singh said that on Monday, heavy rain is expected in Siddharthnagar, Gonda, Balrampur, Shravasti, Bahraich, Lakhimpur Kheri, Sitapur, Mathura, Hathras, Agra, Bareilly, Pilibhit, Shahjahanpur, Sambhal, Badaun, Sant Kabir Nagar, Basti, Maharajganj, Hardoi, Farrukhabad, Kannauj, Kanpur Dehat, Kanpur Nagar, Unnao, Lucknow, Barabanki, Rae Bareli, Amethi, Ayodhya, Saharanpur, Muzaffarnagar, Meerut, Hapur, Bulandshahr, Aligarh, Kasganj, Etah, Firozabad, Mainpuri, Etawah, Auraiya, Bijnor, Amroha, Moradabad, Rampur, Jalaun and surrounding areas.          ALSO READ: Odisha Self-Immolation Case: Two Students Arrested For Abetment, Had Provoked Victim ‘Emotionally And Mentally’     Thunder, Lightning Alert In THESE Districts     There is a possibility of lightning with thunder in Banda, Chitrakoot, Fatehpur, Azamgarh, Mau, Deoria, Gorakhpur, Sant Kabir Nagar, Basti, Kushinagar, Maharajganj, Siddharth Nagar, Gonda, Balrampur, Shravasti, Bahraich, Lakhimpur Kheri, Sitapur, Hardoi, Farrukhabad, Kannauj, Kanpur Dehat, Kanpur Nagar, Unnao, Lucknow, Barabanki, Rae Bareli, Amethi, Sultanpur, Ayodhya, Ambedkar Nagar, Saharanpur, Shamli, Muzaffarnagar, Baghpat, Meerut, Ghaziabad, Hapur, Gautam Buddha Nagar, Bulandshahr, Aligarh, Mathura, Hathras, Kasganj, Etah, Agra, Firozabad, Mainpuri, Etawah, Auraiya, Bijnor, Amroha, Moradabad, Rampur, Bareilly, Pilibhit, Shahjahanpur, Sambhal, Badaun, Jalaun, Hamirpur, Mahoba, Jhansi, Lalitpur and surrounding districts.          ALSO READ: Chennai Power Cut On August 5: TANGEDCO Announces Shutdown In Over 400 Areas On Tuesday; Check List     18.1 mm of rain was recorded in Lucknow till noon on Sunday. By evening, the highest rainfall of 61.5 mm was recorded in Malihabad and 34.7 mm at the airport. From June 1 to August 3, the capital has received 266.7 mm of rain.          On Sunday, a drop in temperature. The maximum temperature in Lucknow fell by 4.8 degrees Celsius to 28.5 degrees Celsius. The maximum temperature in the state was 34.2 degrees Celsius in Meerut, while the maximum temperature in most districts remained below 30 degrees Celsius.
